Separate crescent dough into eight triangles and place on a greased 12-in. round pizza pan with points toward the center; seal perforations. In a bowl, combine the mushrooms and butter; toss to coat. Spoon mushroom mixture over dough. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning. Bake at 375 degrees F for 15-20 minutes or until crust is golden brown and mushrooms are tender,